      "message": "What sort of situations make clamping necessary here?\n\nOn a related note, what\u0027s is your plan to put the colors into the dst gamut?  Which color space do you want the matrix to interpolate the colors in?  Either way I think you can work the gamut transform matrix into this 4x3, but it\u0027ll work in differently depending on whether you want to interpolate in src or dst gamut.  Gradients transform their inputs and so interpolate in dst gamut.\n\nThere\u0027s also a helper append_gamut_transform() which you could call somewhere here.  It requires that its inputs are in range in the src gamut, and will clamp as needed if the transform can take any color out of range of the dst gamut.",
