      "writtenOn": "2017-05-18T02:14:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this file might be easier to follow and debug with this new flow as a separate factory.  By weaving it in here we\u0027re creating a bunch of new code paths but exercising only one, and I think that\u0027s setting ourselves up for unintentional interactions between the two flows.  Why don\u0027t we write up a new entry point tailored for this use case?\n\nSkBlitter* SkRasterPipelineBlitter::Create(const SkPixmap\u0026 dst,\n                                           const SkPaint\u0026 paint,\n                                           SkArenaAlloc* alloc,\n                                           const SkRasterPipeline\u0026 shader,\n                                           bool shader_is_opaque) {\n    // We actively ignore the paint color in this method, acting as if it were opaque.\n    auto blitter \u003d alloc-\u003emake\u003cSkRasterPipelineBlitter\u003e(dst,\n                                                        paint.getBlendMode(),\n                                                        SkPM4f{0,0,0,1});\n\n    blitter-\u003efShader.append(SkRasterPipeline::seed_shader, \u0026blitter-\u003efCurrentY);\n    blitter-\u003efShader.extend(shader);\n    // We\u0027d normally modulate the shader by paint alpha here, but we\u0027re treating it as 1.\n    if (auto colorFilter \u003d paint.getColorFilter()) {\n        colorFilter-\u003eappendStages(\u0026blitter-\u003efShader, dst.colorSpace(), alloc, shader_is_opaque);\n    }\n    return blitter;\n}",
